<TITLE> Tarique 'to appear' at BNP council </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com)Tareque Rahman, senior joint secretary general of BNP, now in London, will appear on video making a statement at the inaugural session of BNP's national council. Goyeshar Chandra Roy, joint secretary general and convener of the publicity sub-committee of BNP, told bdnews24.com: "Tarique's pre-recorded statement will be aired on a big screen." It will come before the address of his mother, BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia, at the inaugural session of the council, said Roy. "The programme has been arranged in that order." Tarique went to London, with his wife and children, to seek medical treatment in September 2007, after being granted bail in a number of cases. He was arrested under emergency powers rules by the past caretaker government. Khaleda's elder son Tarique faces thirteen cases, which include charges of extortion and corruption. b
